  "prompt": "What are some of the most common examples of an imperative sentence?",
  "response": "Imperative sentences are used to give commands, instructions, or make requests. They often imply a subject of \"you\" and end with a period or an exclamation mark. Here are some common examples of imperative sentences:\n\n1. \"Please close the door.\"\n2. \"Sit down.\"\n3. \"Finish your homework.\"\n4. \"Turn off the lights.\"\n5. \"Call me when you get home.\"\n6. \"Don't touch that!\"\n7. \"Listen carefully.\"\n8. \"Pass the salt, please.\"\n9. \"Stay quiet during the movie.\"\n10. \"Read the instructions before starting.\"\n\nThese sentences are direct and concise, focusing on prompting an action or response from the listener.",
